- Chapter image ordering lesson from this project: after updating chapter 3, audit image-type consistency in order. ER/DFD/database-design figures must not be interleaved with runtime screenshots; screenshots belong in implementation chapters unless explicitly framed as UI design and kept out of ER/database subsections.

- Chapter 3 structure lesson from this project: runtime screenshots do not belong in chapter 3. If screenshots are inserted there and end up mixed with ER/DFD/database-design figures, remove them, restore chapter 3 to design-only figures, renumber the figure sequence, and update text references accordingly.

- Final cleanup lesson from this project: after figure-text alignment is fixed, run one more pass for repeated explanatory paragraphs and over-claimed screenshot coverage. The prose should describe only the pages actually shown in the inserted figures.

## Consolidated Thesis Workflow

- Always start from a clean baseline:
  - use the school sample/template as the formatting baseline when authorized
  - use the user's original draft as the content baseline
  - if a generated version becomes polluted, stop patching it and roll back to the clean baseline immediately

- Protect template and front matter:
  - open the template/sample in read-only mode only
  - never modify the template file itself
  - operate only on copied destination files
  - if cover, TOC, originality statement, references, acknowledgements, or appendix title formatting drifts, restore from the original/template instead of hand-rebuilding

- Before any TOC update:
  - audit all heading-styled paragraphs
  - demote any body text, figure-caption paragraph, table-caption paragraph, or empty image-anchor paragraph that was accidentally styled as a heading
  - only then use WPS/Word built-in TOC update
  - after update, verify the TOC contains only real headings and no figures, tables, or body content

- Before any image work:
  - confirm the target caption exists
  - confirm the nearby image anchor exists, or explicitly classify the slot as a missing-image case
  - confirm the replacement image asset exists
  - never insert or replace by fixed paragraph index alone

- After every image insertion or replacement:
  - verify the image is actually embedded in the DOCX
  - verify the next non-empty paragraph is the correct numbered caption
  - verify the caption text matches both the real system and the thesis section semantics

- Chapter-level image rules:
  - chapter 3 must contain design-only figures: architecture, module, use-case, business flow, DFD, ER/data-dictionary/database-design figures
  - chapter 4 contains runtime screenshots and implementation UI evidence
  - do not mix chapter 4 screenshots into chapter 3
  - if chapter 3 gets polluted with screenshots, remove them, renumber the chapter-3 figures, and update the surrounding prose

- Image sizing rules:
  - compute a conservative max width from the actual page width and margins of the target section
  - normalize all inline images to that width or smaller
  - never guess image width by eye
  - after resizing, verify images do not overflow page bounds

- Table rules:
  - if table text appears split, vertically stacked, or looks like it has extra leading spaces, treat it as a layout problem first
  - clear cell paragraph indents and abnormal spacing
  - assign explicit stable column widths
  - reduce table font size where needed
  - only edit table text after layout is stable

- Appendix rules:
  - if appendix code is required, insert it directly under the appendix title and before the originality-statement page
  - remove blank placeholder paragraphs in that interval first
  - verify the appendix contains actual code, not just the appendix title

- Final pre-delivery audit:
  - heading hierarchy audit
  - TOC-only-headings audit
  - image embedded + caption present audit
  - image/program/thesis-semantic alignment audit
  - chapter-3 design-only audit
  - table layout audit
  - appendix content audit
  - duplicate paragraph and over-claim cleanup
